# Lint verification before finishing

After any code change (feature, bug fix, refactor, or test update), verify lint before marking the task complete.

## Required steps

1. Run `make lint` (or `golangci-lint run ./...` if Make is unavailable).
2. Use the IDE linter (`ReadLints`) on every file you edited.
3. Fix all reported issues in changed code before finishing.
4. Re-run lint after fixes until it passes cleanly.

## When to skip

- Question-only or read-only tasks with no file edits.
- The user explicitly asks not to run lint.

## If lint fails

- Fix issues in the current change set; do not disable linters without user approval.
- Report any remaining failures and what blocked a fix.
